^d # logout exit
^l # clear

F11 #full screen

^Shift++ font increase
^- decrease
^arrow word by word move
Alt+Back delete word
Fn Arrow End Home
^+Shift C V copy paste
^y paste
^a begining
^e ending
^u delete before cursor cut
^k delete after cursor cut
^x+e (Multi line command ) opens the current command in editor

## Navigation 🚀

Alt + f/b - Move cursor to previous/next word
Ctrl + a/e - Move cursor to beginning/end of command
Ctrl + xx - Toggle between the start of line and current cursor position
Ctrl + f/b - Move cursor to previous/next character

## Editing ✏️

Ctrl + x,e - Open command in editor
Ctrl + k - Cut till end
Ctrl + u - Delete whole line (zsh)/ cut until beginning (bash)
Alt + w - Delete until beginning (zsh)
Alt + l/u - Lowercase/Uppercase word
Alt + c - Capitalize Word
Ctrl + w - Cut previous word
Alt + Del - Delete previous word
Alt + d - Delete next word
Alt +. or !$ - Previous commands last arguement
!\* - All arguments of previous command
Alt + t - Swap current word with previous
Ctrl + t - Swap the last two characters before the cursor (typo).
Esc + t - Swap the last two words before the cursor
Ctrl + y - Paste
Ctrl + \_ - Undo
Alt + r - Cancel the changes, revert

Ctrl + d Delete character under the cursor
Ctrl + h Delete character before the cursor (Backspace)

Moving the cursor:
Ctrl + p Previous command (Up arrow)
Ctrl + n Next command (Down arrow)

## Process 📊

Ctrl + l - Clear screen
Ctrl + c - Interrupt/Kill
Ctrl + d - Close Current Shell
Ctrl + z - Background/Foreground job

## History ⏳

Ctrl + r - History search
Ctrl + s - Go back to the next most recent command
^abc­^­def - Run previous command, replacing abc with def

## Modes 🕹️

Ctrl +x,v - vi mode (zsh)
set -o vi - Vi mode
set -o emacs
default Emacs setting
